2.text: Peel, pit, and slice the peaches.

3.text: Put the peaches into a large bowl, then stir in the white sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice, and cornstarch.

4.text: Transfer the peach mixture into a 2-quart (2-liter) baking dish, and bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes.

5.text: Combine the flour, white sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, and salt in a separate bowl.

6.text: Cut the butter into the flour mixture until you get a coarse mixture.

7.text: Pour in the water, and stir it with a whisk until it is just combined.

8.text: Spoon the batter over the peaches.

9.text: Make some cinnamon sugar to sprinkle on top.

10.text: Sprinkle the cinnamon-sugar evenly over the cobbler.

11.text: Bake the cobbler for about 30 minutes.

12.text: Let the cobbler cool for a few minutes, then serve warm.

13.text: Wash, peel, and slice the peaches.

14.text: Put the sliced peaches into a large bowl, then stir in the sugar and salt.

15.text: Place the peach mixture into a skillet, and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

16.text: Place the flour into a large bowl, then stir in the sugar and salt.

17.text: Cut the butter into the flour mixture.

18.text: Stir in the buttermilk until the dough just holds together.

19.text: Pat the dough into a disk, then use a glass or a 2½-inch (6.35-centimeter) biscuit cutter to cut out 8 to 12 biscuits.

20.text: Place the biscuits on top of the peaches.

21.text: Cover the cobbler with a tight-fitting lid, and cook it over medium heat for about 20 minutes.

22.text: Let the cobbler cool for 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

25.text: Melt the butter in a 9 by 13-inch (22.86 by 33.02-centimeter) baking dish.

26.text: Combine the peaches, sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a large bowl.

27.text: Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt together in a separate bowl.

28.text: Stir in the milk and the egg using a whisk.

29.text: Pour the batter evenly over the melted butter.

30.text: Pour the peach mixture over the batter, and do not stir.

31.text: Bake the cobbler for 35 to 45 minutes.

32.text: Let the cobbler cool for a few minutes, then serve it warm.
